description: French conclusif, from Late Latin conclusivus, from Latin conclūsīvē (“conclusively”), from past participle of concludere.

adjectives.description: conclusive (comparative more conclusive, superlative most conclusive)

entries.meaning: Providing an end to something; decisive.
examples: The set of premises of a valid argument is conclusive in the sense that no further evidence could possibly be added to the set of premises which would make the argument invalid.
